Comprehensive Application Breakdown: Client Dashboard App
📋 Application Overview
Purpose: This is a CLIENT-FACING dashboard for beauty and wellness services that allows clients to:

Browse service providers (Hairstylists, Barbers, Nail Techs, Massage Therapists)
Book appointments
View provider portfolios
Message providers
Manage their hair history
Search for services by location
Current State: The frontend is complete but NO REAL SERVICE PROVIDERS ARE WIRED IN. It currently uses mock data (providers.json) showing zero providers after location filtering.

🗄️ Database Schema (PostgreSQL)
1. Users Table (users)
- id: varchar (UUID primary key)
- username: text (unique)
- password: text
- email: text (unique)
- fullName: text
- role: text (values: 'client', 'hairstylist', 'barber', 'nail_tech', 'massage_therapist')
- profileImage: text (nullable)
- bio: text (nullable)
- location: text (nullable)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Stores both clients AND service providers. Role determines user type.

2. Service Categories Table (service_categories)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- name: text
- description: text (nullable)
- icon: text (nullable)
- color: text (nullable)
Purpose: Service types (e.g., "Cuts & Styling", "Coloring", "Manicures")

3. Services Table (services)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- hairstylistId: varchar (references users.id)
- categoryId: varchar (references service_categories.id)
- name: text
- description: text (nullable)
- basePrice: decimal(10,2)
- duration: integer (minutes)
- isActive: boolean (default true)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Services offered by individual providers.

4. Bookings Table (bookings)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- clientId: varchar (references users.id)
- hairstylistId: varchar (references users.id)
- serviceId: varchar (references services.id)
- appointmentDate: timestamp
- duration: integer (minutes)
- status: text ('pending', 'confirmed', 'completed', 'cancelled')
- totalPrice: decimal(10,2)
- notes: text (nullable)
- createdAt: timestamp
- updatedAt: timestamp
Purpose: Appointment bookings between clients and providers.

5. Portfolio Images Table (portfolio_images)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- hairstylistId: varchar (references users.id)
- title: text (nullable)
- description: text (nullable)
- beforeImage: text (nullable)
- afterImage: text (required)
- serviceId: varchar (references services.id, nullable)
- tags: json (array of strings)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Before/after images for provider portfolios.

6. Messages Table (messages)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- senderId: varchar (references users.id)
- recipientId: varchar (references users.id)
- bookingId: varchar (references bookings.id, nullable)
- content: text
- messageType: text ('text', 'template', 'image')
- templateId: varchar (nullable)
- isRead: boolean (default false)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Direct messaging between clients and providers.

7. Message Templates Table (message_templates)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- hairstylistId: varchar (references users.id, nullable)
- name: text
- content: text
- category: text ('consultation', 'booking_confirmation', 'aftercare', 'follow_up')
- isDefault: boolean (default false)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Pre-written message templates for providers.

8. Hair History Table (hair_history)
- id: varchar (UUID)
- clientId: varchar (references users.id)
- bookingId: varchar (references bookings.id, nullable)
- hairType: text (nullable)
- hairLength: text (nullable)
- hairColor: text (nullable)
- previousTreatments: json (array of strings)
- allergies: text (nullable)
- preferences: text (nullable)
- notes: text (nullable)
- createdAt: timestamp
Purpose: Track client hair service history and preferences.

🔌 API Endpoints (RESTful)
Service Categories
GET /api/service-categories - List all categories
GET /api/service-categories/:id - Get single category
POST /api/service-categories - Create category
PUT /api/service-categories/:id - Update category
DELETE /api/service-categories/:id - Delete category
Services
GET /api/services?hairstylistId=<id> - List services (optionally filtered by provider)
GET /api/services/:id - Get single service
POST /api/services - Create service
PUT /api/services/:id - Update service
DELETE /api/services/:id - Delete service
Bookings
GET /api/bookings?clientId=<id>&hairstylistId=<id> - List bookings (filtered)
GET /api/bookings/:id - Get single booking
POST /api/bookings - Create booking
PUT /api/bookings/:id - Update booking
PATCH /api/bookings/:id/status - Update booking status
DELETE /api/bookings/:id - Delete booking
Portfolio
GET /api/portfolio/:hairstylistId - Get provider portfolio
GET /api/portfolio/image/:id - Get single image
POST /api/portfolio - Upload portfolio image
PUT /api/portfolio/:id - Update image
DELETE /api/portfolio/:id - Delete image
Messages
GET /api/messages/:userId - Get all messages for user
GET /api/conversations/:userId1/:userId2 - Get conversation between two users
GET /api/messages/single/:id - Get single message
POST /api/messages - Send message
PATCH /api/messages/:id/read - Mark message as read
DELETE /api/messages/:id - Delete message
Message Templates
GET /api/message-templates/:hairstylistId - Get provider templates
GET /api/message-templates/single/:id - Get single template
POST /api/message-templates - Create template
PUT /api/message-templates/:id - Update template
DELETE /api/message-templates/:id - Delete template
Hair History
GET /api/hair-history/:clientId - Get client hair history
GET /api/hair-history/entry/:id - Get single entry
POST /api/hair-history - Create entry
PUT /api/hair-history/:id - Update entry
DELETE /api/hair-history/:id - Delete entry
Service Providers
GET /api/service-providers?role=<role> - List providers (optionally filtered by role)
